painting by @jacobtarazoff | words by me -- She died in the cabin under the eyes of Josie and Henry, her sons. She was forty-five. Henry fourteen. September 16, 1874. It was a Wednesday. Uncle Billy was gone prospecting and so the two brothers dug their mother’s grave without him. From the edge of the cemetery looking in, they must have seemed like little outlines of men.
